<br>
This is pretty obvious once you get a nostromo, but might be worth mentioning for folks who don't have one and who are considering it for general use rather than auto twisting:<br>
<br>
If you want a simple 1 ... 2 ... 3 .... 4 ... twist, including clicky items, without using /stopsong /cast macros on the hotkey pads, this is easy to achieve on the Nostromo. It's not perfect because does require a stopsong button .. but its not bad.<br>
<br>
Essentially it works by writing short non-repeating macros for each key you want to use in the twist. Assume you have mapped the f1 - f4 keys to the songs and/or clicky item slots on the hotpad, and f5 to the stopsong button. Then key 1 on the nostromo would call a short macro like this:<br>
<br>
press f5 [single press of stopsong key]<br>
delay .1 <br>
release f5 <br>
delay .1 <br>
press f1 [song/clicky item 1 start]<br>
delay .1 <br>
release f1 <br>
<br>
(play with delays if necessary)<br>
<br>
Rinse and repeat for all the other songs including clickies.<br>
<br>
This maintains the virtues of 11 .. 22 ... 33... twisting (or 1 ... 12...23..) -- allowing you to see what songs are where on the hotpad, and swap songs in the twist by dragging the gems around, and also allows easy integration of clickies with no change of pattern. And you are still twisting by hand, so all the flexibility is there.<br>
<br>
